Win32-Word-Declarative

Win32::Word::Declarative is a set of functions that permit the definition of Word documents and actions to be taken against them to
be defined in the declarative framework of Class::Declarative.

INSTALLATION

To install this module, run the following commands:

	perl Makefile.PL
	make
	make test
	make install

SUPPORT AND DOCUMENTATION

After installing, you can find documentation for this module with the
perldoc command.

    perldoc Win32::Word::Declarative

You can also look for information at:

    RT, CPAN's request tracker
        http://rt.cpan.org/NoAuth/Bugs.html?Dist=Win32-Word-Declarative

    AnnoCPAN, Annotated CPAN documentation
        http://annocpan.org/dist/Win32-Word-Declarative

    CPAN Ratings
        http://cpanratings.perl.org/d/Win32-Word-Declarative

    Search CPAN
        http://search.cpan.org/dist/Win32-Word-Declarative/


